<div class="container start">
  <div class="row text-center">
    <%= image_tag 'logo.png', width: '250' %>
    <h1>Track-o-Bot</h1>
    <div class="slogan">The easiest way to track your Hearthstone matches</div>
  </div>

  <div class="row text-center">
    <% if defined?(WIN_DOWNLOAD_URL) %>
      <a href="<%= WIN_DOWNLOAD_URL %>" class="btn btn-primary" role="button"><i class='fa fa-windows'></i>&nbsp;Download for Windows</a>
    <% end %>
    <% if defined?(MAC_DOWNLOAD_URL) %>
      <a href="<%= MAC_DOWNLOAD_URL %>" class="btn btn-primary" role="button"><i class='fa fa-apple'></i>&nbsp;Download for Mac</a>
    <% end %>
    <a href="https://github.com/stevschmid/track-o-bot/releases" class="btn btn-default" role="button"><i class='fa fa-bars'></i>&nbsp;Releases</a>
    <a href="https://github.com/stevschmid/track-o-bot" class="btn btn-default" role="button"><i class='fa fa-github'></i>&nbsp;Source Code</a>
    <a href="https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr?cmd=_donations&business=84VEGPBHDHZ6U&lc=US&item_name=Track%2do%2dBot&currency_code=USD&bn=PP%2dDonationsBF%3abtn_donate_LG%2egif%3aNonHosted" class="btn btn-default" role="button"><i class='fa fa-paypal'></i>&nbsp;Donate</a>
  </div>

  <div class="row steps">
    <div class="col-xs-6 col-md-3">
      <%= image_tag 'step_install.png', class: 'step' %>
      <div class="caption">
        1. Install and launch the app
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-xs-6 col-md-3">
      <%= image_tag 'step_play.png', class: 'step' %>
      <div class="caption">
        2. Play Hearthstone
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-xs-6 col-md-3">
      <%= image_tag 'step_profile.png', class: 'step' %>
      <div class="caption">
        3. Open your profile via the <em>Track-o-Bot</em> Icon
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-xs-6 col-md-3">
      <%= image_tag 'step_history.png', class: 'step' %>
      <div class="caption">
        4. See your match history and analyze your games
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="row">
    <h2>Features</h2>
    <p>Track-o-Bot is a small, easy-to-use app which automatically tracks your Hearthstones matches. Install, launch and you are ready to go.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><b>Overlay</b> <span class="label label-success">NEW</span>: Hover over any deck to see which cards were drawn or played during the game!</li>
      <li><b>Stats</b>: Tracks match-ups and results of your Hearthstone battles</li>
      <li><b>History</b>: Records the course of each match (cards played and hero powers used at each turn)</li>
      <li><b>Web profile</b>: Uploads results automatically to your online profile. Use one profile for multiple devices!</li>
      <li><b>Full transparency</b>: Your data belongs to you! Download your history (directly or via API) and analyze your play</li>
      <li><b>Open-source</b>: Contribute and shape the future of Track-o-Bot!</li>
      <li>Low memory footprint (&lt;10 MB) and low CPU usage (&lt;1%)</li>
      <li>Available both on Windows &amp; Mac</li>
      <li>Written in C++ using the <a href="http://www.qt.io/" target="_blank">Qt</a> Framework</li>
    </ul>
    <ul class="gallery">
      <li><%= link_to image_tag('screenshot_history.png'), image_path('screenshot_history.png'), target: '_blank' %></li>
      <li><%= link_to image_tag('screenshot_deck_stats.png'), image_path('screenshot_deck_stats.png'), target: '_blank'  %></li>
      <li><%= link_to image_tag('screenshot_arena.png'), image_path('screenshot_arena.png'), target: '_blank' %></li>
      <li><%= link_to image_tag('screenshot_overlay.jpg'), image_path('screenshot_overlay.jpg'), target: '_blank' %></li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="row">
    <h2>Troubleshooting</h2>
    <ul class="troubleshoot">
      <li><em>Q: It is safe to use?</em><br/><a href="https://twitter.com/bdbrode/status/511151446038179840" target="_blank">Yes.</a></li>
      <li><em>Q: Why doesn't Track-o-Bot track my games?</em><br/>Make sure you restart Hearthstone after you installed or updated Track-o-Bot. Make sure you tell Track-o-Bot the correct path to your Hearthstone location in the settings tab.</li>
      <li><em>Q: Can I use the same account on multiple computers?</em><br/>Yes! Use the import/export function in Track-o-Bot's settings to back up your account credentials.</li>
      <li><em>Q: Where can I see what's going on?</em><br/>There is a log accessible via the settings in Track-o-Bot. Enable the debug mode if you feel frisky.</li>
      <li><em>Q: Does it work on Linux?</em><br/>Check out this <a href="https://github.com/BOSSoNe0013/track-o-bot" target="_blank">fork</a> which includes native support for linux.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="row">
    <h2>Support</h2>
    Use the official <a href="http://www.reddit.com/r/trackobot/" target="_blank">subreddit</a> if you run into problems or want to discuss ideas. Make sure you state the version of Track-o-Bot and the OS you are using.
  </div>

  <div class="row">
    <h2>License</h2>
    The source code for Track-o-Bot is released under the <a href="https://www.gnu.org/licenses/old-licenses/lgpl-2.1.html">GNU Lesser General Public License (LGPL)</a>.
  </div>
</div>

